        the reionization epoch through deep imaging surveys remains
        observationally challenging. The larger area covered by ground-
        based surveys like COSMOS enables the discovery of the brightest
        galaxies at these high redshifts. Covering \$1.4\$deg\$\^2\$,
        our COSMOS catalogues were constructed from the latest
        UltraVISTA data release (DR4) combined with the final
        Spitzer/IRAC COSMOS images and the Hyper-Suprime-Cam Subaru
        Strategic Program DR2 release. We identify \$17\$ new
        \$7.5<z<10\$ candidate sources, and confirm \$15\$ previously
        published candidates. Using deblended photometry extracted by
        fitting surface brightness models on multi-band images, we
